TITLE: German court convicts 97-year-old woman of working as secretary to Nazi SS at concentration camp
SUMMARY: A court in Germany convicted 97-year-old Irmgard Furchner on over 10,000 counts of accessory to murder for working as a secretary to a Nazi SS commander at a concentration camp.

TITLE: Taliban officially bans women from obtaining university education
SUMMARY: The Taliban has banned women in Afghanistan from obtaining a university education,according to Tuesday reports. The move is the Taliban's latest abuse of human rights this year.

TITLE: Putin orders spy agencies to intensify hunt for 'traitors, spies, saboteurs' as war effort in Ukraine falters
SUMMARY: Russian President Vladimir Putin said Tuesday that the Federal Security Services (FSB) will ramp up the hunt for "traitors, spies and saboteurs."

TITLE: Archeologists excavate ancient tomb associated with 'midwife of Jesus' in southwest Jerusalem
SUMMARY: The Jewish burial cave complex traditionally associated with Jesus’ midwife Salome is being excavated in southwest Jerusalem as part or a heritage development project.

TITLE: Sister of North Korea's Kim issues fresh ICBM threat; US flies bombers, stealth jets
SUMMARY: The U.S. military has deployed a group of nuclear-capable bomber planes and stealth aircraft to drill with South Korean forces after the Sunday launch of missiles from North Korea.

TITLE: German government to allow health insurance companies to pay more for medications that are in short supply
SUMMARY: Germany's government will allow insurance companies to pay more than the legally set price for patent-free medication as they are in short supply in the country.

TITLE: Title 42's end could mean big payday for Mexican cartels, according to experts
SUMMARY: The increasingly sophisticated and complex methods that the cartels use make it difficult for border authorities to completely stem the flow of illegal immigrants.

TITLE: Video shows Russian gas pipeline explosion that killed 3
SUMMARY: A gas pipeline explosion in central Russia killed three and sparked concern over further export disruptions to Europe amid gas shortages.

TITLE: Thai officials admit sunken Navy vessel had too few life vests on board
SUMMARY: Thai Navy officials acknowledged that there were not enough live vests aboard the HTMS Sukothai for its 105 sailors when it sank in the Gulf of Thailand on Sunday.

TITLE: Palestinians call for strike in West Bank after prisoner dies of lung cancer
SUMMARY: Palestinians have called for a strike in the occupied West Bank after a prisoner died of lung cancer. Palestine's prime minister accused Israel of “deliberate medical negligence."
